----------------------- Github Actions -----------------

Script Instruction in YAML :- 
- Whenever there is a PUSH.
- SSH into my server
- CD /home/app
- git pull
- docker compose up -d

^ This script will run on the github hosted runners.

---------------------------------------------------

RUN THE SSH Key :- 
- ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com" -->> Best & modern option (Ed25519)

- ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096 -C "your_email@example.com" -->> Alternative (older systems)

--------------------------------------------------------

- After generating the public and private key save the public key on EC2 instance -->> cd .ssh folder -->> paste the public key

- And save the private key as a secrets in setting in github repo.

- and after that ideally we should remove both keys before pushing the changes to github. 

